Write a minInArray function that takes arr as an argument and returns the minimum element of the array.

Use a loop in your solution. The use of the Math.min () method is not permitted.

Example:

minInArray ([3, 4, 8, 1]) eturn 1;
minInArray ([11, 12)  return 11;
minInArray ([1, 1])  return 1;
minInArray ([]) return undefined.

Solution:

function minInArray(arr){
  let min = arr[0];
  for(let i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
    if (arr[i] < min) min = arr[i];
  }
  return min;
}
